10/08/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- A methane gas explosion in a mine killed seven workers on Friday (8 August). Authorities reported that at least 16 others were injured. The incident occurred in Askale, in the eastern province of Erzurum.
In other news, 17 Turkish sailors were rescued after they had to abandon ship about 70 nautical miles off the Greek coast. The Malta-flagged Ogan started to sink after a fire in the engine room. The Greek Coast Guard transported the crew to the nearby town of Pylos. No injuries were reported. (Reuters, AFP, Anadolu Agency - 09/08/03; AP - 08/08/03)
